XMLSysInfo (XSI) is a system monitoring daemon that replies to
network queries with XML-encoded system information and statistics.
Its purpose is to provide a comprehensive overview of a system's
various components, their health, resources, load, and many other
things. It does so equally on all supported platforms. This data
can then be analyzed, graphed or otherwise presented by a front-end,
or put to any other imaginable use. XMLSysInfo is BSD-licensed and
free for anyone to use for any purpose.
